vista.set
Class IrregularTimeSeries

java.lang.Object
  vista.set.TimeSeries
      vista.set.IrregularTimeSeries
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, DataSet, Named
public class IrregularTimeSeries
extends TimeSeries

A default implementation of the data set interface. This class uses an array of x and y doubles to store its elements.

Version:
$Id: IrregularTimeSeries.java,v 1.1 2003/10/02 20:49:25 redwood Exp $
Author:
Nicky Sandhu (DWR).

                           int[] flags,

Constructor for irregular time series

Parameters:
name - The name of the time series. Could be the pathname which then gets parsed into its attributes.
time - An array of time objects
y - An array corresponding to each element of the time array
flags - An array of quality flags [optional]
attr - The data set attributes [optional]

IrregularTimeSeries

public IrregularTimeSeries(java.lang.String name,
                           double[] x,
                           double[] y)
Initializes an irregular time series with the x and y arrays. No new memory is created, only references are held to the two arrays.

Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if x and y array lengths don't match.

IrregularTimeSeries

                           int[] flags)
Initializes a data set with the x and y arrays and with a flag array for each value.

Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if x and y array lengths don't match.

IrregularTimeSeries

public IrregularTimeSeries(TimeSeries ts)
Creates an irregular time series from the given time series. All missing values are removed from the resulting irregular time series. This is the same as calling the constructor with a filter of Constants.DEFAULT_FILTER

IrregularTimeSeries

public IrregularTimeSeries(TimeSeries rts,
                           ElementFilter filter)
creates an irregular time series from a given time series and a filter such that only acceptable values go into creating this irregular time series

IrregularTimeSeries

public IrregularTimeSeries(java.lang.String name,
                           double[] x,
                           double[] y,
                           int[] flags,
                           DataSetAttr attr)
The main constructor for irregular time series.

Parameters:
name - The name of this irregular time series. If this name can be parsed into pathname parts that is done and the resulting parts are used to form the attributes of this irregular time series
x - The array of x values in julian minutes since 30dec1899 2400. This array is held by this irregular time series as opposed to creating a copy
y - The array of y values. This array is held by this irregular time series as opposed to creating a copy.
flags - The array of quality flags
attr - The attributes of this data set
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if x and y array lengths don't match.
